## Git and GitHub ÔÇö do nothing unless the user explicitly asks

**The #1 mistake:** treating ÔÇťsyncÔÇŁ or ÔÇťuploadÔÇŁ as permission to run **git** commands.

| User said | Agent may do | Agent must NOT do |
|-----------|--------------|-------------------|
| ÔÇťsyncÔÇŁ, ÔÇťuploadÔÇŁ, ÔÇťpush to SurfaceÔÇŁ | **scp scripts only** (`sync-to-pc.sh`, `sync-to-dgx.ps1`, etc.) | `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, merge `upstream`, open PRs |
| ÔÇťcommitÔÇŁ | `git add` + `git commit` (local only) | `git push` unless user also says push |
| ÔÇťpush to GitHubÔÇŁ | User does it (agent has no GitHub SSH key) | Any `git push` / `gh` write |

After the `.env` leak, the user **removed the agent SSH key from GitHub**. Never assume GitHub write access.

**DGX and Surface are the same project folder on two machines** ÔÇö keep them aligned with **sync scripts over SSH**, not with git remotes or upstream.

## DGX Ôćö Surface file copy (scp) ÔÇö auto-run after edits

**User permission:** After every create/edit/delete in this repo, **run the correct scp sync script yourself** (do not ask the user to run it). This is **not** git ÔÇö never use `git push` / `git pull` / `upstream` for machine sync.

| You edited on | Run automatically |
|---------------|-------------------|
| **DGX** ÔÇö DGX-owned files (docs, README, Pitch Deck) | `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` |
| **DGX** ÔÇö `src/` (DGX was sole editor; lock if needed) | `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-src --retry-until-complete` |
| **Surface** ÔÇö PC-owned files (`src/`, scripts, roadmaps) | `.\scripts\sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete` |
| **Surface** ÔÇö Pitch Deck only | `.\scripts\sync-pitch-deck-to-dgx.ps1` (also auto from sync-changes when git shows Pitch Deck changes) |
| **Surface** ÔÇö need DGX docs/scripts | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` |

**Never tell the user to run sync** ÔÇö you run it. Pitch Deck: `.cursor/rules/pitch-deck-sync-protected.mdc`. Forbidden: `scp -r "Pitch Deck" host:/repo/`.

From DGX, Surface sync can run via SSH if you are on DGX but changed Surface-owned files through remote commands.

Say **ÔÇťcopied to SurfaceÔÇŁ** / **ÔÇťcopied to DGXÔÇŁ** in chat ÔÇö never say ÔÇťgit pushÔÇŁ for scp sync.

**Still forbidden without explicit user ask:** `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, merge `upstream`, PRs, GitHub publish.

## After DGX-owned changes

Run automatically: `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` (add `--include-src` only when DGX owned `src/` edits). Full `sync-to-pc.sh` only when incremental is insufficient.

## After Surface-owned changes

Run automatically on Surface: `.\scripts\sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete`. Respect single-writer rules for `src/`; do not overwrite Surface `src/` from DGX without lock/sync rules.
